{{Ref improve|date=June 2013}} The '''Bunsen–Kirchhoff Award''' is a prize for "outstanding achievements" in the field of analytical [[spectroscopy]]. It has been awarded since 1990 by the German Working Group for Applied Spectroscopy, and is endowed with {{Euro|2500}} by [[PerkinElmer]], [[Germany]].<ref name="winners">{{cite web|url=http://barolo.ipc.uni-tuebingen.de/extern/dasp/daspbunsen_eng.html |title=Bunsen Kirchhoff Preis |publisher=German Working Group of Applied Spectroscopy |date= |accessdate=4 July 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gwu.edu/~media/pressreleases/12-27-00-BKPrize.cfm |title=Press Release Archive: Prestigious Bunsen-Kirchhoff Prize Awarded To GW Student |publisher=[[George Washington University]] |date=14 March 2001 |accessdate=4 July 2013}}</ref> The prize is named in honor of chemist [[Robert Bunsen]] and physicist [[Gustav Kirchhoff]].
