'''Photomutagenicity''' is the property of being '''photomutagenic''', in that when irradiated by visible or [[UV light]], a '''photomutagenic''' chemical substance (''e.g''., [[umbelliferone]]) - found in or on an organism - can cause [[mutation]](s) of that particular organism. Other photomutagenic substances include [[furocoumarin]]s and [[limettin]].<ref>{{cite journal|last1=Raquet|first1=N|last2=Schrenk|first2=D|title=Relative photomutagenicity of furocoumarins and limettin in the hypoxanthine phosphoribosyl transferase assay in V79 cells.|journal=Chemical Research in Toxicology|date=September 2009|volume=22|issue=9|pages=1639–47|pmid=19725558}}</ref>

