'''Raymond Robert Rogers''' is a professor and [[Professor|chair]] of geology at [[Macalester College]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.press.uchicago.edu/ucp/books/author/R/R/au5457460.html|title=Raymond R. Rogers|date=12 December 2012|website=Press.uchicago.edu|accessdate=6 November 2014}}</ref> He earned his B.S. in geology from [[Northern Arizona University]] in 1985, his M.S. from the [[University of Montana]] in 1989, and his Ph.D. from the [[University of Chicago]] in 1995<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.macalester.edu/geology/People/Ray/cv.pdf |title=Archived copy |access-date=2011-04-07 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120927154246/http://www.macalester.edu/geology/People/Ray/cv.pdf |archive-date=2012-09-27 |dead-url=yes |df= }}</ref> Rogers' specializations are as a [[sedimentary geology|sedimentary geologist]] and [[taphonomy|taphonomist]], with a focus on the study of terrestrial and marginal marine depositional systems, particularly those with abundant fossils.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.macalester.edu/geology/People/Ray/ray.html|title=Professor Rogers webpage|website=Macalester.ed|accessdate=6 November 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141124144344/http://www.macalester.edu/geology/People/Ray/ray.html|archive-date=2014-11-24|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref> He is one of the editors of the book ''Bonebeds: Genesis, Analysis, and Paleobiological Significance'', from the [[University Of Chicago Press]] (2008).
==References== ;Notes {{reflist}} ;Sources *''Bonebeds: Genesis, Analysis, and Paleobiological Significance'', Raymond R. Rogers, David A. Eberth and [[Anthony Fiorillo|Anthony R. Fiorillo]], University Of Chicago Press, 2008, {{ISBN|978-0-226-72371-6}}
