'''Theodor Friedrich Julius Basiner''' (3 January 1816&ndash;14 October 1862) was a [[Baltic Germans|Baltic German]] botanist who lived and worked mainly in [[Russian Empire|Imperial Russia]].

==Life and work==
Theodor Friedrich Julius Basiner was born in [[Tartu]], present-day [[Estonia]], and studied at [[Tartu University]] between 1836 and 1840. In 1843 he became a conservator at the [[Saint Petersburg Botanical Garden|Botanical Garden]] in [[Saint Petersburg]]. He kept this position until 1845, when he became the institution's librarian. In 1849 he moved to a new position in [[Kiev]], present-day [[Ukraine]]. In 1842-43 he made a scientific journey to [[Khiva]] in present-day [[Uzbekistan]]. He died in [[Vienna]], [[Austria]].<ref name="BBL">{{cite web |url= http://www.bbl-digital.de/eintrag/Basiner-Theodor-Friedrich-Julius-1816-1862/|title= Basiner, Theodor Friedrich Julius|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |language= German|website= Baltisches Biographisches Lexikon digital|publisher= Baltischen Historischen Kommission|accessdate=4 June 2015}}</ref>

==Selected writings==
* ''Naturwissenschaftliche Reise durch die Kirgisensteppe nach Chiva''

