{{Infobox scientist | name = Yojiro Kimura| image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_date = 1912| birth_place = | death_date =  {{Death year and age|2006|1912}} | death_place = | residence = | citizenship = | nationality = Japanese| fields = [[Botany]] | workplaces = | alma_mater = | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | known_for = | author_abbrev_bot = Y.Kimura| author_abbrev_zoo = | influences = | influenced = | awards = | signature = <!--(filename only)--> | signature_alt = | footnotes = | spouse = }}

'''Yojiro Kimura''' (1912 – 2006){{sfn|HUH|2015}} was a Japanese botanist, known for his [[taxonomic classification|classification]] of [[monocotyledons]],{{sfn|Dahlgren|Clifford|1982}}{{sfn|Lam|1959|loc=[https://books.google.ca/books?id=gQvLBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA58 p.&nbsp;58]}} and of Japanese species of ''[[Hypericum]]''.{{sfn|Robson|2007}}

== Selected publications ==
* Kimura, Y. 1953. The system and phylogenetic tree of plants. J. Jpn. Bot. 28: 97–104.
* Kimura, Y. 1956. Système et phylogénie des monocotyledones. Notulae Systematicae, Herbier du Muséum de Paris 15:137–159.{{sfn|Kimura|1956}}
* Kimura, Y. "Shokubutsu bunrui taikei no rekishi" [The History of Botanical Classification Systems] in "Seibutsugakushi ronshu" [Essays on The History of Biology]), (Yasaka Shobo, 1987).
* Kimura, Y. "Natsurarisuto no keifu", (Chuou Kouron Sha, Inc., 1983)

== Legacy ==
Yojiro Kimura is the authority for 58 taxa, such as ''[[Hypericum nagasawae|Hypericum hayatae]]'' <small>Y.Kimura</small>{{sfn|Tropicos|2015|loc=[http://www.tropicos.org/Person/6130?tab=names Kimura, Yojiro]}}

